Today we have a new design for the desktop apps to make Moo.do more intuitive and more attractive. There are small tweaks all over the app but the most notable changes are:




Top buttons moved into a sidebar. This makes it clearer what the buttons do and we think it’s prettier :). Toggle the sidebar with Cmd + Option + S on Mac and Ctrl + Shift + I on Windows or Linux, and you can still access the buttons by hotkey.
Rearranged pane header. The titles are on the first row and search is on the second row, with the search box and filters split to make them more distinct.
Improved workspace switching. Open the boards menu with Ctrl + B and use the arrow keys to switch between them.
